### Selection Rationale
Represents unique probe of neutrino physics at astrophysical scales with sensitivity to both solar processes and fundamental neutrino properties. Independent measurement context from accelerator-based experiments. Exceptional statistical power from continuous solar neutrino flux. Potential sensitivity to novel directional effects in neutrino propagation or detection.
